d expansion, its effects on Native populations, European versus Native cartography, cultural definitions of space, and communication of traditions. Belyea also introduces Peter Fidler as an important documentary source for exploration studies during the fur trade expansion, incorporating into her own study Fidler's journals, maps, and reports, most of which are previously unpublished.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFur tradezCanadaxHistory. 0aFur tradezWest (U.S.)xHistory. 7aHISTORY / North America.2bisacsh  aearly European settlers.  aearly European traders.  aearly cartography of north America.  aearly maps of north America.  aearly north American fur trade.  afirst contact in the Americas.  afur trade Canada.  afur trade history.  ahistorical maps.  ahudsons bay company fur trade.  alewis and clark expedition.  alewis and clark.  amapping north America.  aold maps of north America.  apeter fidler and the metis.  apeter fidler book.  apeter fidler map.  apeter fidler.  apeter filder journal.  avoyagers fur trade.  avoyagerus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552383247?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552383247423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552383247/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles